stina Felix Douyon</p><p class="text-gray-600">Pulmonologist, Haiti</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the Patient Mobile App in the Virtual Practice?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Patient Mobile App is the native iOS and Android application that comes with your Virtual Practice. It lets patients securely log in, book appointments, view health records, pay bills, and communicate with providers — all from their smartphones."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the Patient Mobile App free for clinics to use?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Every Virtual Practice includes access to the free ContinuousCare patient app, which patients can download from the iOS App Store or Google Play. Clinics don't need to pay extra for their patients to use it."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I have the app under my own brand name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Startups and clinics that want their own branded app can choose the white-label option. This paid add-on publishes the app under your organization's App Store and Play Store accounts, with your name, logo, and branding."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What can patients do with the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients can:\n\nBook video or in-person appointments\n\nView prescriptions, test results, and medical history\n\nReceive smart notifications and reminders\n\nPay bills online\n\nManage family member accounts\n\nSync health data automatically from supported devices"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the app integrate with Apple Health and Google Health Connect?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients can grant permission to sync data from Apple Health (iOS) or Google Health Connect (Android) directly into their Virtual Practice health record. White-label apps also support additional Bluetooth 